        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "٢٣١. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام) فِي قَوْلِ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:145:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/231/279",
        "text": [
          "هِ تَعَالَى ﴿إِنَّ اللهَ يَأْمُرُ بِالْعَدْلِ وَالْإِحْسَانِ﴾: الْعَدْلُ الْإِنْصَافُ، وَالْإِحْسَانُ التَّفَضُّلُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "231. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said about Allāh’s saying: Verily, Allāh enjoins justice (‘adl) and benevolence (iḥsān),(Qur’ān,16:90). Here ‘adl means equidistribution and iḥsān means favour."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
